video-only prerecorded violation.

00:12:27.960 --> 00:12:31.070
Here is an overlay button trigger
with an icon of a paper boat

00:12:31.070 --> 00:12:35.720
or a hat and the visible text,
customized accessibility,

00:12:35.720 --> 00:12:39.620
the browser dev tools
indicated has focus, but thanks

00:12:39.620 --> 00:12:44.260
to an outline, non-important,
there's no visible style.

00:12:44.260 --> 00:12:47.133
That's a 2.4.7 focus
visible failure.

00:12:50.200 --> 00:12:53.340
The boat icon image has alt text.

00:12:53.340 --> 00:12:55.730
The alt text does not
describe the image,

00:12:55.730 --> 00:12:59.280
instead it reads manage
display settings.

00:12:59.280 --> 00:13:02.590
That feels like a 1.1.1
non-text content failure to me.

00:13:03.780 --> 00:13:05.910
That makes the full
accessible name of the button

00:13:07.080 --> 00:13:09.820
"Manage display settings
Customized Accessibility",

00:13:11.324 --> 00:13:13.029
but the button has an ARIA label,

00:13:13.029 --> 00:13:15.995
reading FACIL'iti
colon adapt display,

00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:20.880
which overrides the text we can
see, which is a 2.5.3 label

00:13:20.880 --> 00:13:21.880
and name failure.

00:13:22.730 --> 00:13:24.980
That's three WCAG
failures on the button

00:13:24.980 --> 00:13:28.620
that triggers the accessibility
features from the overlay vendor.

