Koena declined to comply with
the request and wrote about why.

00:27:19.070 --> 00:27:21.260
Another disabled user
who I'm not naming here,

00:27:21.260 --> 00:27:24.210
but I've shared their plight on
Twitter, was subpoenaed to appear

00:27:24.210 --> 00:27:25.510
in court.

00:27:25.510 --> 00:27:31.100
FACIL'iti had asked for 5,000
in damages, 55,000 and fines,

00:27:31.100 --> 00:27:33.280
and in order to cease
comments that may

00:27:33.280 --> 00:27:35.854
"discredit the FACIL'iti solution."

00:27:37.150 --> 00:27:38.750
I cannot think of a
better way to prove

00:27:38.750 --> 00:27:42.520
that your product helps disabled
users than by suing disabled people

00:27:42.520 --> 00:27:43.520
who say it does not.

00:27:45.530 --> 00:27:48.760
That story got some press
in France in Numerama

00:27:48.760 --> 00:27:52.440
with the machine translated
headline, FACIL'iti, the Solution

00:27:52.440 --> 00:27:55.030
for Online Inclusion
That Refuses Criticism?

00:27:57.240 --> 00:28:00.390
Another overlay vendor threatened
a lawsuit for valid criticism,

00:28:00.390 --> 00:28:02.690
specifically AudioEye.

00:28:02.690 --> 00:28:05.430
You can read the AudioEye's
cease and desist letter to me,

00:28:05.430 --> 00:28:11.950
along with my response on my site,
which I do believe I link at the end.

00:28:14.740 --> 00:28:18.250
Overlay vendors also claim
that organizations love them,

00:28:18.250 --> 00:28:20.770
but community and industry
organizations have been clear

00:28:20.771 --> 00:28:21.610
that they do not.

00:28:23.530 --> 00:28:26.790
National Federation of the Blind
after accepting one as a sponsor

00:28:26.790 --> 00:28:30.260
