00:29:56.020 --> 00:29:57.682
We've gathered together
some new experts

00:29:57.683 --> 00:29:58.980
who are helping us to fix this.

00:29:58.980 --> 00:30:00.830
It would be great to have
your support going forward

00:30:00.830 --> 00:30:03.250
to make the next iteration
a complete success."

00:30:06.260 --> 00:30:08.930
Many overlay vendors claimed
that detractors are really

00:30:08.930 --> 00:30:11.370
just frustrated competitors.

00:30:11.370 --> 00:30:12.950
The Overlay Fact
Sheet disproves that.

00:30:13.970 --> 00:30:17.360
Over 750 people have
signed it so far.

00:30:17.360 --> 00:30:19.770
You could sign it after this talk.

00:30:19.770 --> 00:30:22.310
They represent web
specification contributors,

00:30:22.310 --> 00:30:26.080
internal accessibility experts
from companies in higher education,

00:30:26.080 --> 00:30:29.710
lawyers for the disabled,
contributors to assistive technology,

00:30:29.710 --> 00:30:31.090
and end users with disabilities.

00:30:32.350 --> 00:30:35.340
I encourage you to visit the
site at overlayfactsheet.com

00:30:35.340 --> 00:30:38.760
and read through the information
and links that identify strengths

00:30:38.760 --> 00:30:42.070
and weaknesses of overlay
widgets and automated repair.

00:30:42.070 --> 00:30:45.270
It also touches on technical
and privacy concerns.

00:30:45.270 --> 00:30:47.830
In addition to the signatures,
there are statements from users.

00:30:50.360 --> 00:30:52.140
There is one
professional organization

00:30:52.140 --> 00:30:54.730
for digital accessibility
practitioners.

00:30:54.730 --> 00:30:58.120
International Association of
Accessibility Professionals, IAAP,

00:30:59.600 --> 00:31:04.340
is a division of G3ict, the Global
Initiative for Inclusive Information

00:31:04.340 --> 00:31:06.640
and Communication Technologies.

00:31:06.640 --> 00:31:08.450
It allows membership
for overlay vendors.

00:31:09.510 --> 00:31:12.211
Overlay vendors then brand
their marketing materials

00:31:12.211 --> 00:31:13.572
with the IAAP logo.

00:31:14.670 --> 00:31:17.530
Similarly,
the W3C allows for anyone to set up

00:31:17.530 --> 00:31:19.190
an unaffiliated community group.

00:31:20.340 --> 00:31:23.690
Overlay vendors use these
as veneers of credibility.

00:31:25.400 --> 00:31:29.030
Some organizations display
the IAAP logo in their footer.

00:31:29.030 --> 00:31:32.180
UserWay and Max Access
each do so using the weight

00:31:32.180 --> 00:31:34.620
of accessibility professionals
as a marketing boost.

00:31:35.720 --> 00:31:41.740
Others might get promotional
consideration as AudioEye did

00:31:41.740 --> 00:31:47.260
when IAAP tweeted an AudioEye post,
a post incidentally arguably lifted

00:31:47.260 --> 00:31:48.860
from W3C documents.

00:31:50.670 --> 00:31:53.810
There was finally some
fallout though for IAAP.

00:31:53.810 --> 00:32:01.610
On January 17, few months ago,
IAAP promised a "proactive" response

00:32:01.610 --> 00:32:05.550
to that tweet and overlay membership,
even though I raised the concern

00:32:05.550 --> 00:32:09.190
in September along with
others, in September of 2021.

00:32:10.260 --> 00:32:12.770
It produced a survey from
members and non-members.

00:32:12.770 --> 00:32:15.270
The results of that survey
were posted on Friday,

00:32:15.270 --> 00:32:17.950
February 25th of this year.

00:32:17.950 --> 00:32:24.280
Of the 609 responses 591,
97% were not overlay vendors.

00:32:24.280 --> 00:32:30.000
81% of them, 478 responses state they
do not compete with overlay vendors.

00:32:31.160 --> 00:32:37.340
549 responses or 90% say they have
seen false claims by overlay vendors,

00:32:37.340 --> 00:32:42.430
and 533 responses or 86%
believe IAAP should comment

00:32:42.430 --> 00:32:44.710
on marketing claims in general.

00:32:44.710 --> 00:32:49.040
Also 90%, 549 respondents
believe IAAP should comment

00:32:49.040 --> 00:32:51.400
on overlay marketing
claims specifically.

00:32:54.430 --> 00:32:57.690
In May, representatives from
UserWay and AudiEye proposed

00:32:57.690 --> 00:33:02.490
an overlay community group to the
W3C and got the votes approval

00:33:02.490 --> 00:33:05.820
and call for participation
of in 12 hours.

00:33:05.820 --> 00:33:09.180
The next day it deleted the call
for participation and sat dormant.

00:33:10.340 --> 00:33:14.640
Almost a month later, it renamed
itself to Accessibility at the Edge

00:33:14.640 --> 00:33:18.020
and used a novel interpretation
of Edge computing to justify

00:33:18.020 --> 00:33:20.550
and obfuscate its purpose.

00:33:20.550 --> 00:33:23.960
Two months after that, it reposted
its call for participation,

00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:27.220
this time framing it as an
accessibility community group

00:33:27.220 --> 00:33:31.610
that just happens to include
overlays, and so overlays veneer

00:33:31.610 --> 00:33:34.100
of a W3C blessing is complete.

00:33:35.920 --> 00:33:38.995
This community group
then got a breakout slot

00:33:38.996 --> 00:33:40.800
at W3C's Technical Plenary

00:33:40.800 --> 00:33:45.130
and Advisory Committee or
TPAC session in September.

00:33:45.130 --> 00:33:48.270
There, the UserWay COO
took three opportunities

00:33:48.270 --> 00:33:51.290
to promote its own
product in this session.

00:33:51.290 --> 00:33:54.140
This despite every
attendee, except for one

00:33:54.140 --> 00:33:56.348
of the community
groups invited guests,

00:33:56.349 --> 00:34:00.410
voicing their broad opposition
to overlays for an hour.

00:34:03.190 --> 00:34:06.200
As we have seen,
overlays cannot make your site

00:34:06.200 --> 00:34:07.620
or your brand better overnight.

00:34:08.750 --> 00:34:12.110
To wrap up this talk, I want to
cover some steps you can undertake

00:34:12.110 --> 00:34:13.150
without overlays.

00:34:14.900 --> 00:34:15.900
Plan ahead.

00:34:17.530 --> 00:34:18.530
Have a drink of water.

00:34:21.860 --> 00:34:22.860
