00:34:23.940 --> 00:34:24.850
Plan ahead.

00:34:24.850 --> 00:34:28.180
Hire a consultant who has
some experience in the space.

00:34:28.180 --> 00:34:31.600
They can help you choose a vendor
who prioritizes accessibility

00:34:31.600 --> 00:34:33.490
and write this into your contracts.

00:34:33.490 --> 00:34:36.910
They can also direct you to
technologies that have been vetted.

00:34:36.910 --> 00:34:39.870
Some platforms have
accessible features already.

00:34:39.870 --> 00:34:45.350
Last I checked, WordPress offers 114
free accessibility-ready themes built

00:34:45.350 --> 00:34:47.460
with a baseline of
compliance already in place.

00:34:48.960 --> 00:34:55.310
Some free online resources, when you
create content, use those resources.

00:34:55.310 --> 00:34:58.000
They may have all you
need to get going.

00:34:58.000 --> 00:35:00.680
There is even a free tool to
generate an accessibility statement

00:35:00.680 --> 00:35:03.590
for your site provided
by the very organization

00:35:03.590 --> 00:35:05.200
that sets accessibility standards.

00:35:07.290 --> 00:35:09.270
What if you already have a site?

00:35:09.270 --> 00:35:12.260
You can use one of the many free
automated accessibility checkers

00:35:12.260 --> 00:35:14.720
on the market, assuming you
aren't interested in getting

00:35:14.720 --> 00:35:16.740
into the browser's own tools.

00:35:16.740 --> 00:35:21.920
There's ARC, Axe, Lighthouse,
WAVE, and webhint among others.

00:35:21.920 --> 00:35:25.300
While they will not catch all
the issues, maybe only about 30%,

00:35:25.300 --> 00:35:27.640
they will at least give you
a sense where you stand.

00:35:28.970 --> 00:35:31.180
Where you have gaps, document them.

00:35:31.180 --> 00:35:33.900
Identify what is wrong and put
together a plan and timeline

00:35:33.900 --> 00:35:35.300
to address them.

00:35:35.300 --> 00:35:39.380
Publish that on your site when you
generate an accessibility statement.

00:35:39.380 --> 00:35:42.100
As long as you're under the
timelines you provide, you can choose

00:35:42.100 --> 00:35:45.060
what your ongoing budget
will be to address them,

00:35:45.060 --> 00:35:46.720
even if it's only $1,000 per year.

00:35:49.520 --> 00:35:51.920
If you are affected by
overlays as a consumer,

00:35:51.920 --> 00:35:53.930
then you can take some action.

00:35:53.930 --> 00:35:57.010
In the US, the Federal Trade
Commission has rules that advertising

00:35:57.010 --> 00:36:01.930
must not be deceptive, must include
evidence and cannot be unfair.

00:36:01.930 --> 00:36:04.830
Overlayfalseclaims.com
provides documented examples

00:36:04.830 --> 00:36:10.070
of overlay vendor false claims, along
with consumer complaint resources

00:36:10.070 --> 00:36:14.250
for the US, Federal and State,
Canada, and New Zealand.

00:36:14.250 --> 00:36:17.890
You can use information there to
file a false advertising complaint.

00:36:17.890 --> 00:36:21.520
You can also open up here to submit
information for filing complaints

00:36:21.520 --> 00:36:22.520
in other countries.

