00:44:44.410 --> 00:44:47.430
As we know,
a lot of businesses that are backed

00:44:47.430 --> 00:44:52.010
by venture funds aren't
necessarily fully fleshed out.

00:44:52.010 --> 00:44:55.440
In many cases, they're still building
the airplane as they're falling

00:44:55.440 --> 00:44:56.580
out of the sky.

00:44:56.580 --> 00:44:59.100
I think that's sort of the
scenario that we're seeing here.

00:44:59.100 --> 00:45:04.800
When you have a startup culture,
the move-fast-and-break-things model

00:45:04.800 --> 00:45:10.080
doesn't apply to the kind of rigor
that is necessary for dealing

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:11.240
with humans.

00:45:11.240 --> 00:45:13.629
Accessibility is not really
a technology problem,

00:45:13.630 --> 00:45:14.680
it's a human problem.

00:45:15.840 --> 00:45:16.630
That's where we have it.

